      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HEZA DOOZIE (3) raced in a handy position last time out and fought on well to finish runner-up, beaten 2.6 metres at this venue. Suited dropping to a distance where he owns a good record and another nice draw should ensure a cosy run. Could go one better. JAYJAYBENNY (8) took his record at this circuit and distance to three from four when winning two back before a solid third last week at Newcastle, beaten 4.6 metres. If things go his way from the back row he is good enough to take out a race like this. ROCK FISHERMAN (10) cops a tougher draw but missed narrowly when second at his most recent appearance at this circuit and distance. KING HIT NZ (1) has been coming from wider barriers of late but was edged out narrowly the last time he started on the pegs.",
